<hr> <heading1><a href="http://www.stayorswitch.com/blog/can-you-open-the-secret-passageway-in-time/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Can you open the secret passageway in time?">Can you open the secret passageway in time?</a></heading1></br>
<heading4>September 15th, 2016</heading4>
<p><p><a href="http://stayorswitch.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Rome_passetto_night_inside.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-186" src="http://stayorswitch.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Rome_passetto_night_inside-300x218.jpg" alt="rome_passetto_night_inside" width="300" height="218" srcset="http://www.stayorswitch.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Rome_passetto_night_inside-300x218.jpg 300w, http://www.stayorswitch.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Rome_passetto_night_inside-768x558.jpg 768w, http://www.stayorswitch.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Rome_passetto_night_inside-1024x744.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>
<p>You&#8217;re in an upstairs hallway of Trump mansion looking at what must be 101 books. You&#8217;re not supposed to be here. The party&#8217;s downstairs, why did you even come up here in the first place? Oh yeah, you overheard someone mention a secret passageway triggered by pulling two books at the same time on the mahogany bookshelf. You estimate that you can test two book pairs each second. On average, how long will it take you to get through the passageway and achieve unknowable glory?</p>

<div class='easySpoilerWrapper' style='border-color:#7c7c7c;'>
<table class='easySpoilerTable' border='0' style='text-align:center;' align='center' bgcolor='FFFFFF' >

<tr style='white-space:normal;'>
<th class='easySpoilerTitleA' style='white-space:normal;font-weight:bold;text-align:left;vertical-align:middle;font-size:100%;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border-color:#7c7c7c;color:#f4f4f4;'><a href='blog' onclick='wpSpoilerToggle("spoilerDiv4c728001",true,"Show Solution","Hide Solution","fast",false); return false;' onselectstart='return false;' style='text-decoration: none;color:#f4f4f4;'>Show/Hide Solution</a></th>
<th class='easySpoilerTitleB'style='padding:0px;text-align:right;vertical-align:middle;font-size:100%;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border-color:#7c7c7c; white-space:nowrap;'><a href='blog'  class='easySpoilerButton' style='font-size:100%;color:#f4f4f4;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border: 1px inset;border-style:solid;border-color:#7c7c7c;display:none; margin: 3px 0px 3px; padding: 4px; ' align='right'>Select</a><a href='blog'  id='spoilerDiv4c728001_action' class='easySpoilerButtonBare' value="Show Solution" align='right' style='font-size:100%;color:#f4f4f4;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border: 1px inset;border-style:solid;border-color:#7c7c7c;display:none; margin: 3px 0px 3px 5px; padding: 4px;'>Show Solution</></th>
</tr>
<tr><td class='easySpoilerRow' colspan='2' style='border-color:#7c7c7c;'><div id='spoilerDiv4c728001' class='easySpoilerSpoils'  style='display:none; white-space:wrap; overflow:auto; vertical-align:middle;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;color:#f4f4f4;border-color:#7c7c7c;'>
 About 21 minutes. You&#8217;re gonna be up there a while. Why?</p>
<p>With 101 books, there are 5,050 combinations of two books possible: To make a pair, there are 101 books for the first choice and then 100 books available for the second choice. 101 x 100 = 10,100. However, we double-counted because Book A and Book B is the same pair as Book B and Book A (aka order doesn&#8217;t matter) so we need to divide our result by the number of ways that two items can be arranged&#8211;two. So 10,100 / 2 = 5,050. The alternate method is using the combinations formula for C(101, 2), or &#8220;Combinations, 101 choose 2.&#8221; C(101, 2) = 101! / ((101 &#8211; 2)! 2!) = 5,050.</p>
<p>So we now have to calculate the expected number of the 5,050 pairs we will need to try in order to open the passageway. When looking for something in a group of <em>n</em> choices, it will take on average (<em>n</em> + 1) / 2 tries, which is also the average of the integers from 1 to <em>n</em>. In this case, that&#8217;s 5051/2, or 2525.5 tries.</p>
<p>At two attempts per second, that&#8217;ll take on average 2525.5/2 = 1262.75 seconds, or about 21 minutes. But it could take you less than a second or more than 42 minutes!</p>
<p>
</div></td></tr>
</table>
<div class='easySpoilerConclude' style='border-color:#7c7c7c;'><table class='easySpoilerTable' border='0' style='text-align:center;' frame='box' align='center' bgcolor='FFFFFF'><tr><th class='easySpoilerEnd' style='width:100%;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border-color:#7c7c7c;'></th><td class='easySpoilerEnd' style='white-space:nowrap;background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border-color:#7c7c7c;' colspan='2'></td></tr><tr><td class='easySpoilerGroupWrapperLastRow' colspan='2' style='background-color:#7c7c7c;background-image:none;border-color:#7c7c7c;'></td></tr></table></div>
</div>

